						               													<description>A mystery scene of an incident &amp;#10;Suspicious suspects...&amp;#10;...and you!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Take part in the case and find the hidden truth!&amp;#10;Or..maybe.. &amp;#10;Are you the culprit?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In &amp;lsquo;Catch Crime&amp;rsquo;, all players become one of the suspects and have to investigate to find out the hidden truth. Cases could be a crime or other peculiar situations.&amp;#10;The concept of &amp;lsquo;Catch Crime&amp;rsquo; is based on &amp;lsquo;Mafia game&amp;rsquo; widely played among Koreans. We wanted to add storytelling and evidence-based deduction game elements to it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Alliance or enemy?&amp;#10;&amp;lsquo;Catch Crime&amp;rsquo; can be a cooperating game or a competing game. How would you know it? You have to find out for yourself based on the situation in the game, behaviors of the other player and other evidence!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How many players?&amp;#10;3-4 players get to play in &amp;lsquo;Catch Crime&amp;rsquo;. They play as a character they each chose to be.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How do you find evidence?&amp;#10;Evidence is given in diverse forms such as player&amp;rsquo;s character information, plot description, evidence cards, and even with the other player&amp;rsquo;s behaviors. So, try not to miss out on anything in the game. Be doubtful!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
